'''Victoria Lidbom''' (October 31, 1940 - June TBD, 1985) was an Australian wildlife expert, outdoorswoman, zookeeper and veterinarian. A curious explorer since childhood, she initially struggled to afford her passions due to various financial responsibilities. This changed when she received a big inheritance from her late father, which she used to open her zoo, Lidbom's Sanctuary. 

==Childhood==
Lidbom was born in the City of Knox to firewoman Aurora Lidbom (1906 - TBD) and senior Army enlistee Gavin Lidbom (1885 - 1962). She had an older brother named Eric (born 1936), a teacher. 

